Objective: To implement the English Program for primary school students with the following specific tasks:
• Assist English teachers in preparing teaching aids, learning tools, and materials for lesson plans;
• Assist English teachers in managing and decorating the classroom;
• Assist English teachers with administrative tasks:
● Send notices to parents;
● Complete files on students’ behavior and academic performance assessments.
Coordinate with English teachers in the following specific tasks:
Before class or events
• Based on the school year event calendar, proactively plan the schedule for organizing student events;
• Coordinate with English teachers to carry out and complete preparation tasks before the class or event takes place (planning, decoration, teaching aids, learning materials, etc.).
During class and events
• The English Teaching Assistant must always be present in the classroom and during events with the English Teacher;
• Assist the English teacher in building positive student behavior by implementing pre-existing plans in the program and demonstrating model and expected behaviors for students;
• Assist English teachers during one-on-one sessions (guiding students in completing worksheets and practicing in station-based learning sessions); manage the classroom and implement events according to the plan;
• Assist teachers in identifying issues related to student behavior and English language acquisition, and report in a timely manner.
After class or events
• Summarize lessons/events, remind students as requested by the English teacher;
• Clean up and store learning materials or stationery after class and events.
Other administrative tasks:
• Arrange the classroom according to the lesson objectives;
• Take daily attendance, evaluate students in the format required by the English teacher when necessary;
• Organize and preserve books in the reading area;
• Check the condition and inventory of learning materials and classroom supplies;
• Assist English teachers in decorating the classroom;
• Store and display students’ works and assignments throughout the school year.

Job Requirements:
